import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    zip_code_counts = data['zip_code'].value_counts()
    zip_code_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Zip Code')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes in the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_counts = data['city'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(city_counts.index, city_counts.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('City')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of cities in the dataset?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    labels = state_counts.index.tolist()
    sizes = state_counts.values.tolist()
    fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots()
    ax1.pie(sizes, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    ax1.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of states in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    county_counts = data['county'].value_counts()
    ax = county_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('County')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.axhline(y=county_counts.median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of counties in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], s=10, alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between latitude and longitude?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
